   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Thirty A SAVIOR WHO FORGIVES AND JUSTIFIES Scripture: Acts 13:38-39 The futility of depending upon works The human disposition is corrupted.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Although man would do good, his goodness has a limit.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Sometimes he might be able to do a little bit of good, but even that he can never do perfectly.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Human works are imperfect and defiled.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>In fact, man has no power to do good.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Even in honoring our parents, our motive within is impure.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Therefore, no man is justified in the presence of God by his own works.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The trustworthiness of Christ s forgiveness The death of Christ resolves the problem of man s sins.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The resurrection of Christ enables man to obtain the position and life of justification.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Christ, by His death, has paid the ransom for man s sins, therefore He is able to forgive sins.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Because of Christ s position and life in resurrection, He is able to justify man.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Therefore, the Scripture says, that through this man is proclaimed unto you remission of sins: and by Him everyone that believeth is justified from all things.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>How to obtain Christ s forgiveness and justification Confess that you are sinful, and that you have no strength to do good.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Confess that Christ has died and resurrected for you.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Receive Christ as your Savior.</S>
   </TEXT>
